  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(<=3g) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: for Termination  (Drug Court)

15CF250, 16CF226, 16CF253 also at this time. 9:08 Drug Court Team present, DA Sean Froelich in court, defendant present, in custody. Hearing being conducted on motion to terminate.  DA Froelich addresses the court--reviews requirements of last chance contract that was signed by defendant; defendant has had prior violations and violations of last chance agreement; team requests termination due to nature of violations and violation of agreement, team feels that there is nothing more that Drug Court can offer the defendant.  9:13 Defendant addresses the court regarding her sobriety and time in Drug Court, realizes faults and has been working on correcting her violations, defendant wants to change, realizes her success is due to Drug Court and would like to remain in the program.  Court addresses the defendant, realizes that defendant has learned and sometimes the hard way; relapse is not the problem, the main problem is the dishonesty; group has high hopes for the defendant; there is not anything more Drug Court can do and notes violations of the contract; Court terminates the defendant from the Pierce County Drug Court program.  Court will prepare an Order for Termination. Adjourned 09:21.

10:07 Alisa present in court, drug court team present, DA Froelich in court.  Heaing on team's motion Hearing on teams motion for Alisas participation in the program.  Judge reviews process, motion to terminate made at team meeting, team has decided to proceed with termination, Alisa has spoken with the team regarding termination. Team has made recommendation to terminate participation. Judge explains Alisa's right to an attorney, Alisa states she does not wish to have an attorney represent her today. Court finds that Alisa waives her right to an attorney.  Court summarizes grounds for termination; continued dishonesty, contact with people she is not allowed to have contact with.
Froelich addresses the court on behalf of the team regarding motion for termination and violations.  Froelich recommends moving forward with the termination process.  Alisa addresses the court and team and would like to remain in the program for structure and guidance. Judge addresses Alisa. Off the record 10:22. Back on the record 10:28.  Judge will provide a written contract to Alisa and give her one more chance, if Alisa signs the contract she can remain in the program, no dishonesty or violations of the contract will be tolerated.  Written contract will be provided before next week. 10:29
